<title>Downloads</title>
<p>This page explains all options for configuring Downloads in Preferences in <app>Parabolic</app>.</p>


<terms>
    <item>
        <title>Maximum Number of Active Downloads</title>
        <p>The number of active downloads allowed to run at a time. Must be an integer value between 1 and 10.</p>
        <p>If the max number of active downloads is reached, Parabolic will place new downloads in a queue until more downloads are able to be run.</p>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Valor per defecte: 5</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Sobreescriu els fitxers existents</title>
        <p>If enabled, Parabolic will overwrite existing files.</p>
        <p>For example, if a file named <code>movie.mp4</code> exists in the download folder, and a new download is created named <code>movie</code>, <code>movie.mp4</code> will be overwritten with the new download's content.</p>
        <note>
            <p>Parabolic will detect downloads that should be resumed and avoid this setting when recovering or retrying failed downloads</p>
        </note>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Valor per defecte: activat</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Limit Filename Characters</title>
        <p>Restricts characters in filenames to only those supported by Windows.</p>
        <p>This option is only available on Linux.</p>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Valor per defecte: desactivat</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Included Media Id in Title After Validation</title>
        <p>Whether or not to included the media's id in the title (file name) when validated.</p>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Valor per defecte: activat</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Included Auto-Generated Subtitles</title>
        <p>Whether or not to included subtitles that are auto-translated to fit the requested subtitle languages.</p>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Valor per defecte: activat</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Preferred Video Codec</title>
        <p>The video codec Parabolic should prefer when parsing media formats to download.</p>
        <note>
            <p>If Parabolic cannot find any formats with the selected preferred codec, no video formats will be available for download.</p>
        </note>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Default: Any</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Preferred Audio Codec</title>
        <p>The audio codec Parabolic should prefer when parsing media formats to download.</p>
        <note>
            <p>If Parabolic cannot find any formats with the selected preferred codec, no audio formats will be available for download.</p>
        </note>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Default: Any</p>
        </note>
    </item>
    <item>
        <title>Format de subt√≠tols preferits</title>
        <p>The file format Parabolic should ensure all downloaded subtitles are downloaded as.</p>
        <note style="advanced">
            <p>Default: Any</p>
        </note>
    </item>
</terms>
